pokemon.description: It has a pliable body without any bones. If any part of its body is torn off, it grows right back.

pokemon.name: Ambipom
pokemon.description: To eat, it deftly shucks nuts with its two tails. It rarely uses its arms now.

pokemon.name: Drifloon
pokemon.description: A Pokémon formed by the spirits of people and Pokémon. It loves damp, humid seasons.

pokemon.name: Drifblim
pokemon.description: It's drowzy in daytime, but flies off in the evening in big groups. No one knows where they go.

pokemon.name: Buneary
pokemon.description: It slams foes by sharply uncoiling its rolled ears. It stings enough to make a grown-up cry in pain.

pokemon.name: Lopunny
pokemon.description: An extremely cautious Pokémon. It cloaks its body with its fluffy ear fur when it senses danger.

pokemon.name: Mismagius
pokemon.description: Its cries sound like incantations. Those hearing it are tormented by headaches and hallucinations.

pokemon.name: Honchkrow
pokemon.description: Becoming active at night, it is known to swarm with numerous Murkrow in tow.

pokemon.name: Glameow
pokemon.description: It claws if displeased and purrs when affectionate. Its fickleness is very popular among some.

pokemon.name: Purugly
pokemon.description: It is a brazen brute that barges its way into another Pokémon's nest and claims it as its own.

pokemon.name: Chingling
pokemon.description: It emits cries by agitating an orb at the back of its throat. It moves with flouncing hops.

pokemon.name: Stunky
pokemon.description: It protects itself by spraying a noxious fluid from its rear. The stench lingers for 24 hours.

pokemon.name: Skuntank
pokemon.description: It sprays a vile-smelling fluid from the tip of its tail to attack. Its range is over 160 feet.

pokemon.name: Bronzor
pokemon.description: Implements shaped like it were discovered in ancient tombs. It is unknown if they are related.

pokemon.name: Bronzong
pokemon.description: One caused a news sensation when it was dug up at a construction site after a 2,000-year sleep.

pokemon.name: Bonsly
pokemon.description: It looks as if it is always crying. It is actually adjusting its body's fluid levels by eliminating excess.

pokemon.name: Mime Jr.
pokemon.description: It habitually mimics foes. Once mimicked, the foe cannot take its eyes off this Pokémon.

pokemon.name: Happiny
pokemon.description: It loves round white things. It carries an egg-shaped rock in imitation of Chansey.

pokemon.name: Chatot
pokemon.description: It can learn and speak human words. If they gather, they all learn the same saying.

pokemon.name: Spiritomb
pokemon.description: A Pokémon that was formed by 108 spirits. It is bound to a fissure in an odd keystone.

pokemon.name: Gible
pokemon.description: It nests in small, horizontal holes in cave walls. It pounces to catch prey that stray too close.

pokemon.name: Gabite
pokemon.description: There is a long-held belief that medicine made from its scales will heal even incurable illnesses.

pokemon.name: Garchomp
pokemon.description: When it folds up its body and extends its wings, it looks like a jet plane. It flies at sonic speed.

pokemon.name: Munchlax
pokemon.description: It wolfs down its weight in food once a day, swallowing food whole with almost no chewing.

pokemon.name: Riolu
pokemon.description: The aura that emanates from its body intensifies to alert others if it is afraid or sad.

pokemon.name: Lucario
pokemon.description: It has the ability to sense the auras of all things. It understands human speech.

pokemon.name: Hippopotas
pokemon.description: It lives in arid places. Instead of perspiration, it expels grainy sand from its body.

pokemon.name: Hippowdon
pokemon.description: It blasts internally stored sand from ports on its body to create a towering twister for attack.

pokemon.name: Skorupi
pokemon.description: It grips prey with its tail claws and injects poison. It tenaciously hangs on until the poison takes.

pokemon.name: Drapion
pokemon.description: It has the power in its clawed arms to make scrap of a car. The tips of its claws release poison.

pokemon.name: Croagunk
pokemon.description: Its cheeks hold poison sacs. It tries to catch foes off guard to jab them with toxic fingers.

pokemon.name: Toxicroak
pokemon.description: Its knuckle claws secrete a toxin so vile that even a scratch could prove fatal.

pokemon.name: Carnivine
pokemon.description: It attracts prey with its sweet-smelling saliva, then chomps down. It takes a whole day to eat prey.

pokemon.name: Finneon
pokemon.description: After long exposure to sunlight, the patterns on its tail fins shine vividly when darkness arrives.

pokemon.name: Lumineon
pokemon.description: It lives on the deep-sea floor. It attracts prey by flashing the patterns on its four tail fins.

pokemon.name: Mantyke
pokemon.description: A friendly Pokémon that captures the subtle flows of seawater using its two antennae.

pokemon.name: Snover
pokemon.description: It lives on snowy mountains. Having had little contact with humans, it is boldly inquisitive.

pokemon.name: Abomasnow
pokemon.description: It whips up blizzards in mountains that are always buried in snow. It is the abominable snowman.

pokemon.name: Weavile
pokemon.description: They live in cold regions, forming groups of four or five that hunt prey with impressive coordination.

pokemon.name: Magnezone
pokemon.description: It evolved from exposure to a special magnetic field. Three units generate magnetism.

pokemon.name: Lickilicky
pokemon.description: It wraps things with its extensible tongue. Getting too close to it will leave you soaked with drool.

pokemon.name: Rhyperior
pokemon.description: It puts rocks in holes in its palms and uses its muscles to shoot them. Geodude are shot at rare times.

pokemon.name: Tangrowth
pokemon.description: It ensnares prey by extending arms made of vines. Losing arms to predators does not trouble it.

pokemon.name: Electivire
pokemon.description: It pushes the tips of its two tails against the foe, then lets loose with over 20,000 volts of power.

pokemon.name: Magmortar
pokemon.description: It blasts fireballs of over 3,600 degrees F from the ends of its arms. It lives in volcanic craters.

pokemon.name: Togekiss
pokemon.description: It will never appear where there is strife. Its sightings have become rare recently.

pokemon.name: Yanmega
pokemon.description: By churning its wings, it creates shock waves that inflict critical internal injuries to foes.

pokemon.name: Leafeon
pokemon.description: Just like a plant, it uses photosynthesis. As a result, it is always enveloped in clear air.

pokemon.name: Glaceon
pokemon.description: As a protective technique, it can completely freeze its fur to make its hairs stand like needles.

pokemon.name: Gliscor
pokemon.description: It observes prey while hanging inverted from branches. When the chance presents itself, it swoops!

pokemon.name: Mamoswine
pokemon.description: Its impressive tusks are made of ice. The population thinned when it turned warm after the ice age.

pokemon.name: Porygon-Z
pokemon.description: Additional software was installed to make it a better Pokémon. It began acting oddly, however.

pokemon.name: Gallade
pokemon.description: A master of courtesy and swordsmanship, it fights using extending swords on its elbows.

pokemon.name: Probopass
pokemon.description: It exudes strong magnetism from all over. It controls three small units called Mini-Noses.

pokemon.name: Dusknoir
pokemon.description: The antenna on its head captures radio waves from the world of spirits that command it to take people there.

pokemon.name: Froslass
pokemon.description: It freezes foes with an icy breath nearly -60 degrees F. What seems to be its body is actually hollow.

pokemon.name: Rotom
pokemon.description: Its body is composed of plasma. It is known to infiltrate electronic devices and wreak havoc.

pokemon.name: Uxie
pokemon.description: Known as “The Being of Knowledge.” It is said that it can wipe out the memory of those who see its eyes.

pokemon.name: Mesprit
pokemon.description: Known as “The Being of Emotion.” It taught humans the nobility of sorrow, pain, and joy.

pokemon.name: Azelf
pokemon.description: Known as “The Being of Willpower.” It sleeps at the bottom of a lake to keep the world in balance.

pokemon.name: Dialga
pokemon.description: It has the power to control time. It appears in Sinnoh-region myths as an ancient deity.

pokemon.name: Palkia
pokemon.description: It has the ability to distort space. It is described as a deity in Sinnoh-region mythology.

pokemon.name: Heatran
pokemon.description: It dwells in volcanic caves. It digs in with its cross-shaped feet to crawl on ceilings and walls.

pokemon.name: Regigigas
pokemon.description: There is an enduring legend that states this Pokémon towed continents with ropes.

pokemon.name: Giratina
pokemon.description: A Pokémon that is said to live in a world on the reverse side of ours. It appears in an ancient cemetery.

pokemon.name: Cresselia
pokemon.description: Shiny particles are released from its wings like a veil. It is said to represent the crescent moon.

pokemon.name: Phione
pokemon.description: A Pokémon that lives in warm seas. It inflates the flotation sac on its head to drift and search for food.

pokemon.name: Manaphy
pokemon.description: Born on a cold seafloor, it will swim great distances to return to its birthplace.

pokemon.name: Darkrai
pokemon.description: It can lull people to sleep and make them dream. It is active during nights of the new moon.

pokemon.name: Shaymin
pokemon.description: It lives in flower patches and avoids detection by curling up to look like a flowering plant.

pokemon.name: Arceus
pokemon.description: It is described in mythology as the Pokémon that shaped the universe with its 1,000 arms.

pokemon.name: Victini
pokemon.description: This Pokémon brings victory. It is said that Trainers with Victini always win, regardless of the type of encounter.

pokemon.name: Snivy
pokemon.description: They photosynthesize by bathing their tails in sunlight. When they are not feeling well, their tails droop.

pokemon.name: Servine
pokemon.description: They avoid attacks by sinking into the shadows of thick foliage. They retaliate with masterful whipping techniques.

pokemon.name: Serperior
pokemon.description: They raise their heads to intimidate opponents, but only give it their all when fighting a powerful opponent.

pokemon.name: Tepig
pokemon.description: It blows fire through its nose. When it catches a cold, the fire becomes pitch-black smoke instead.

pokemon.name: Pignite
pokemon.description: Whatever it eats becomes fuel for the flame in its stomach. When it is angered, the intensity of the flame increases.

pokemon.name: Emboar
pokemon.description: It can throw a fire punch by setting its fists on fire with its fiery chin. It cares deeply about its friends.

pokemon.name: Oshawott
pokemon.description: The scalchop on its stomach is made from the same elements as claws. It detaches the scalchop for use as a blade.

pokemon.name: Dewott
pokemon.description: Scalchop techniques differ from one Dewott to another. It never neglects maintaining its scalchops.

pokemon.name: Samurott
pokemon.description: Part of the armor on its anterior legs becomes a giant sword. Its cry alone is enough to intimidate most enemies.

pokemon.name: Patrat
pokemon.description: Extremely cautious, they take shifts to maintain a constant watch of their nest. They feel insecure without a lookout.

pokemon.name: Watchog
pokemon.description: They make the patterns on their bodies shine in order to threaten predators. Keen eyesight lets them see in the dark.

pokemon.name: Lillipup
pokemon.description: The long hair around its face provides an amazing radar that lets it sense subtle changes in its surroundings.

pokemon.name: Herdier
pokemon.description: It loyally follows its Trainer's orders. For ages, they have helped Trainers raise Pokémon.

pokemon.name: Stoutland
pokemon.description: This extremely wise Pokémon excels at rescuing people stranded at sea or in the mountains.

pokemon.name: Purrloin
pokemon.description: Its cute act is a ruse. When victims let down their guard, they find their items taken. It attacks with sharp claws.

pokemon.name: Liepard
pokemon.description: Stealthily, it sneaks up on its target, striking from behind before its victim has a chance to react.

pokemon.name: Pansage
pokemon.description: It shares the leaf on its head with weary-looking Pokémon. These leaves are known to relieve stress.

pokemon.name: Simisage
pokemon.description: Ill tempered, it fights by swinging its barbed tail around wildly. The leaf growing on its head is very bitter.

pokemon.name: Pansear
pokemon.description: This Pokémon lives in caves in volcanoes. The fire within the tuft on its head can reach 600º F.

pokemon.name: Simisear
pokemon.description: A flame burns inside its body. It scatters embers from its head and tail to sear its opponents.

pokemon.name: Panpour
pokemon.description: It does not thrive in dry environments. It keeps itself damp by shooting water stored in its head tuft from its tail.

pokemon.name: Simipour
pokemon.description: The high-pressure water expelled from its tail is so powerful, it can destroy a concrete wall.

pokemon.name: Munna
pokemon.description: It eats the dreams of people and Pokémon. When it eats a pleasant dreams, it expels pink-colored mist.

pokemon.name: Musharna
pokemon.description: With the mist from its forehead, it can create shapes of things from dreams it has eaten.

pokemon.name: Pidove
pokemon.description: These Pokémon live in cities. They are accustomed to people. Flocks often gather in parks and plazas.

pokemon.name: Tranquill
pokemon.description: Many people believe that, deep in the forest where Tranquill live, there is a peaceful place where there is no war.

pokemon.name: Unfezant
pokemon.description: Males have plumage on their heads. They will never let themselves feel close to anyone other than their Trainers.

pokemon.name: Blitzle
pokemon.description: When thunderclouds cover the sky, it will appear. It can catch lightning with its mane and store the electricity.

pokemon.name: Zebstrika
pokemon.description: This ill-tempered Pokémon is dangerous because when it's angry, it shoots lightning from its mane in all directions.

pokemon.name: Roggenrola
pokemon.description: They were discovered a hundred years ago in an earthquake fissure. Inside each one is an energy core.

pokemon.name: Boldore
pokemon.description: Because its energy was too great to be contained, the energy leaked and formed orange crystals.

pokemon.name: Gigalith
pokemon.description: The solar energy absorbed by its body's orange crystals is magnified internally and fired from its mouth.

pokemon.name: Woobat
pokemon.description: Suction from its nostrils enables it to stick to cave walls during sleep. It leaves a heart-shaped mark behind.

pokemon.name: Swoobat
pokemon.description: Anyone who comes into contact with the ultrasonic waves emitted by a courting male experiences a positive mood shift.

pokemon.name: Drilbur
pokemon.description: It makes its way swiftly through the soil by putting both claws together and rotating at high speed.

pokemon.name: Excadrill
pokemon.description: More than 300 feet below the surface, they build mazelike nests. Their activity can be destructive to subway tunnels.

pokemon.name: Audino
pokemon.description: Its auditory sense is astounding. It has a radar-like ability to understand its surrounding through slight sounds.

pokemon.name: Timburr
pokemon.description: These Pokémon appear at building sites and help out with construction. They always carry squared logs.

pokemon.name: Gurdurr
pokemon.description: They strengthen their bodies by carrying steel beams. They show off their big muscles to their friends.

pokemon.name: Conkeldurr
pokemon.description: They use concrete pillars as walking canes. They know moves that enable them to swing the pillars freely in battle.

pokemon.name: Tympole
pokemon.description: By vibrating its cheeks, it emits sound waves imperceptible to humans. It uses the rhythm of these sounds to talk.

pokemon.name: Palpitoad
pokemon.description: It lives in the water and on land. It uses its long, sticky tongue to capture prey.

pokemon.name: Seismitoad
pokemon.description: It increases the power of its punches by vibrating the bumps on its fists. It can turn a boulder to rubble with one punch.

pokemon.name: Throh
pokemon.description: When they encounter foes bigger than themselves, they try to throw them. They always travel in packs of five.

pokemon.name: Sawk
pokemon.description: Tying their belts gets them pumped and makes their punches more destructive. Disturbing their training angers them.

pokemon.name: Sewaddle
pokemon.description: This Pokémon makes clothes for itself. It chews up leaves and sews them with sticky thread extruded from its mouth.

pokemon.name: Swadloon
pokemon.description: It protects itself from the cold by wrapping up in leaves. It stays on the move, eating leaves in forests.

pokemon.name: Leavanny
pokemon.description: It keeps its eggs warm with heat from fermenting leaves. It also uses leaves to make warm wrappings for Sewaddle.

pokemon.name: Venipede
pokemon.description: It discovers what is going on around it by using the feelers on its head and tail. It is brutally aggresive.

pokemon.name: Whirlipede
pokemon.description: It is usually motionless, but when attacked, it rotates at high speed and then crashes into its opponent.

pokemon.name: Scolipede
pokemon.description: Highly aggressive, it uses the claws near its neck to dig into its opponents and poison them.

pokemon.name: Cottonee
pokemon.description: They go wherever the wind takes them. On rainy days, their bodies are heavier, so they take shelter beneath big trees.

pokemon.name: Whimsicott
pokemon.description: Riding whirlwinds, they appear. These Pokémon sneak through gaps into houses and cause all sorts of mischief.

pokemon.name: Petilil
pokemon.description: Since they prefer moist, nutrient-rich soil, the areas where Petilil live are known to be good for growing plants.

pokemon.name: Lilligant
pokemon.description: The fragrance of the garland on its head has a relaxing effect. It withers if a Trainer does not take good care of it.

pokemon.name: Basculin
pokemon.description: Red and blue Basculin usually do not get along, but sometimes members of one school mingle with the other's schooL.

pokemon.name: Sandile
pokemon.description: It moves along below the sand's surface, except for its nose and eyes. A dark membrane shields its eyes from the sun.

pokemon.name: Krokorok
pokemon.description: The special membrane covering its eyes can sense the heat of objects, so it can see its surroundings, even in darkness.

pokemon.name: Krookodile
pokemon.description: It can expand the focus of its eyes, enabling it to see objects in the far distance as if it were using binoculars.

pokemon.name: Darumaka
pokemon.description: Darumaka's droppings are hot, so people used to put them in their clothes to keep themselves warm.

pokemon.name: Darmanitan
pokemon.description: When weakened in battle, it transforms into a stone statue. Then it sharpens its mind and fights on mentally.

pokemon.name: Maractus
pokemon.description: Arid regions are their habitat. They move rhythmically, making a sound similar to maracas.

pokemon.name: Dwebble
pokemon.description: It makes a hole in a suitable rock. If that rock breaks, the Pokémon remains agitated until it locates a replacement.

pokemon.name: Crustle
pokemon.description: It possesses legs of enormous strength, enabling it to carry heavy slabs for many days, even when crossing arid land.

pokemon.name: Scraggy
pokemon.description: It immediately headbutts anyone that makes eye contact with it. Its skull is massively thick.

pokemon.name: Scrafty
pokemon.description: It can smash concrete blocks with its kicking attacks. The one with the biggest crest is the group leader.

pokemon.name: Sigilyph
pokemon.description: The guardians of an ancient city, they use their psychic power to attack enemies that invade their territory.

pokemon.name: Yamask
pokemon.description: These Pokémon arose from the spirits of people interred in graves in past ages. Each retains memories of its former life.

pokemon.name: Cofagrigus
pokemon.description: They pretend to be elaborate coffins to teach lessons to grave robbers. Their bodies are covered in pure gold.

pokemon.name: Tirtouga
pokemon.description: About 100 million years ago, these Pokémon swam in oceans. It is thought they also went on land to attack prey.

pokemon.name: Carracosta
pokemon.description: Incredible jaw strength enables them to chew up steel beams and rocks along with their prey.

pokemon.name: Archen
pokemon.description: Revived from a fossil, this Pokémon is thought to be the ancestor of all bird Pokémon.

pokemon.name: Archeops
pokemon.description: It runs better than it flies. It catches prey by running at speeds comparable to those of an automobile.

pokemon.name: Trubbish
pokemon.description: The combination of garbage bags and industrial waste caused the chemical reaction that crated this Pokémon.

pokemon.name: Garbodor
pokemon.description: They absorb garbage and make it part of their bodies. They shoot a poisonous liquid from their right-hand fingertips.

pokemon.name: Zorua
pokemon.description: To protect themselves from danger, they hide their true identities by transforming into people and Pokémon.

pokemon.name: Zoroark
pokemon.description: Each has the ability to fool a large group of people simultaneously. They protect their lair with illusory scenery.

pokemon.name: Minccino
pokemon.description: These Pokémon prefer a tidy habitat. They are always sweeping and dusting, using their tails as brooms.

pokemon.name: Cinccino
pokemon.description: Their white fur feels amazing to touch. Their fur repels dust and prevents static electricity from building up.

pokemon.name: Gothita
pokemon.description: They intently observe both Trainers and Pokémon. Apparently, they are looking at something that only Gothita can see.

pokemon.name: Gothorita
pokemon.description: Starlight is the source of their power. At night, they mark star positions by using psychic power to float stones.

pokemon.name: Gothitelle
pokemon.description: They can predict the future from the placement and movement of the stars. They can see Trainers' life spans.

pokemon.name: Solosis
pokemon.description: Because their bodies are enveloped in a special liquid, they can survive in any environment.

pokemon.name: Duosion
pokemon.description: When their brains, now divided in two, are thinking the same thoughts, these Pokémon exhibit their maximum power.

pokemon.name: Reuniclus
pokemon.description: These remarkably intelligent Pokémon fight by controlling arms that can grip with rock-crushing power.

pokemon.name: Ducklett
pokemon.description: When attacked, it uses its feathers to splash water, escaping under cover of the spray.

pokemon.name: Swanna
pokemon.description: It administers sharp, powerful pecks with its bill. It whips its long neck to deliver forceful repeated strikes.

pokemon.name: Vanillite
pokemon.description: This Pokémon formed from icicles bathed in energy from the morning sun. It sleeps buried in snow.

pokemon.name: Vanillish
pokemon.description: It conceals itself from enemy eyes by creating many small ice particles and hiding among them.

pokemon.name: Vanilluxe
pokemon.description: If both heads get angry simultaneously, this Pokémon expels a blizzard, burying everything in snow.

pokemon.name: Deerling
pokemon.description: The turning of the seasons changes the color and scent of this Pokémon's fur. People use it to mark the seasons.

pokemon.name: Sawsbuck
pokemon.description: The plants growing on its horns change according to the season. The leaders of the herd possess magnificent horns.

pokemon.name: Emolga
pokemon.description: They live on treetops and glide using the inside of a cape-like membrane while discharging electricity.

pokemon.name: Karrablast
pokemon.description: When they feel threatened, they spit an acidic liquid to drive attackers away. This Pokémon targets Shelmet.

pokemon.name: Escavalier
pokemon.description: These Pokémon evolve by wearing the shell covering of a Shelmet. The steel armor protects their whole body.

pokemon.name: Foongus
pokemon.description: For some reason, this Pokémon resembles a Poké Ball. They release poison spores to repel those who try to catch them.

pokemon.name: Amoonguss
pokemon.description: They show off their Poké Ball caps to lure prey, but very few Pokémon are fooled by this.

pokemon.name: Frillish
pokemon.description: They paralyze prey with poison, then drag them down to their lairs, five miles below the surface.

pokemon.name: Jellicent
pokemon.description: They propel themselves by expelling absorbed seawater from their bodies. Their favorite food is life energy.

pokemon.name: Alomomola
pokemon.description: Floating in the open sea is how they live. When they find a wounded Pokémon, they embrace it and bring it to shore.

pokemon.name: Joltik
pokemon.description: They attach themselves to large-bodied Pokémon and absorb static electricity, which they store in an electric pouch.

pokemon.name: Galvantula
pokemon.description: They employ an electrically charged web to trap their prey. While it is immobilized by shock, they leisurely consume it.

pokemon.name: Ferroseed
pokemon.description: They stick their spikes into cave walls and absorb the minerals they find in the rock.

pokemon.name: Ferrothorn
pokemon.description: They attach themselves to cave ceilings, firing steel spikes at targets passing beneath them.

pokemon.name: Klink
pokemon.description: Interlocking two bodies and spinning around generates the energy they need to live.

pokemon.name: Klang
pokemon.description: Spinning minigears are rotated at high speed and repeatedly fired away. It is dangerous if the gears don't return.

pokemon.name: Klinklang
pokemon.description: The gear with the red core is rotated at high speed for a rapid energy charge.

pokemon.name: Tynamo
pokemon.description: These Pokémon move in schools. They have an electricity-generating organ, so they discharge electricity if in danger.

pokemon.name: Eelektrik
pokemon.description: These Pokémon have a big appetite. When they spot their prey, they attack it and paralyze it with electricity.

pokemon.name: Eelektross
pokemon.description: With their sucker mouths, they suck in prey. Then they use their fangs to shock the prey with electricity.

pokemon.name: Elgyem
pokemon.description: This Pokémon had never been seen until it appeared from far in the desert 50 years ago.

pokemon.name: Beheeyem
pokemon.description: It uses psychic power to control an opponent's brain and tamper with its memories.

pokemon.name: Litwick
pokemon.description: While shining a light and pretending to be a guide, it leeches off the life force of any who follow it.

pokemon.name: Lampent
pokemon.description: It arrives near the moment of death and steals spirit from the body.

pokemon.name: Chandelure
pokemon.description: Being consumed in Chandelure's flame burns up the spirit, leaving the body behind.

pokemon.name: Axew
pokemon.description: They mark their territory by leaving gashes in trees with their tusks. If a tusk breaks, a new one grows in quickly.

pokemon.name: Fraxure
pokemon.description: Their tusks can shatter rocks. Territory battles between Fraxure can be intensely violent.

pokemon.name: Haxorus
pokemon.description: Their sturdy tusks will stay sharp even if used to cut steel beams. These Pokémon are covered in hard armor.

pokemon.name: Cubchoo
pokemon.description: Its nose is always running. It sniffs the snot back up because the mucus provides the raw material for its moves.

pokemon.name: Beartic
pokemon.description: It freezes its breath to create fangs and claws of ice to fight with. Cold northern areas are its habitat.

pokemon.name: Cryogonal
pokemon.description: They are born in snow clouds. They use chains made of ice crystals to capture prey.

pokemon.name: Shelmet
pokemon.description: It evolves when bathed in an electric-like energy along with Karrablast. The reason is still unknown.

pokemon.name: Accelgor
pokemon.description: Having removed its heavy shell, it becomes very light and can fight with ninja-like movements.

pokemon.name: Stunfisk
pokemon.description: It conceals itself in the mud of the seashore. Then it waits. When prey touch it, it delivers a jolt of energy.

pokemon.name: Mienfoo
pokemon.description: They have mastered elegant combos. As they concentrate, their battle moves become swifter and more precise.

pokemon.name: Mienshao
pokemon.description: They use the long fur on their arms as a whip to strike their opponents.

pokemon.name: Druddigon
pokemon.description: It races through narrow caves, using its sharp claws to catch prey. Then skin on its face is harder than a rock.

pokemon.name: Golett
pokemon.description: These Pokémon are thought to have been created by the science of an ancient and mysterious civilization.

pokemon.name: Golurk
pokemon.description: It is said that Golurk were ordered to protect people and Pokémon by the ancient people who made them.

pokemon.name: Pawniard
pokemon.description: They fight at Bisharp's command. They cling to their prey and inflict damage by sinking their blades into it.

pokemon.name: Bisharp
pokemon.description: Bisharp pursues prey in the company of a large group of Pawniard. Then Bisharp finishes off the prey.

pokemon.name: Bouffalant
pokemon.description: They charge wildly and headbutt everything. They headbutts have enough destructive force to derail a train.

pokemon.name: Rufflet
pokemon.description: They will challenge anything, even strong opponents, without fear. Their frequent fights help them become stronger.

pokemon.name: Braviary
pokemon.description: The more scars they have, the more respect these brave soldiers of the sky get from their peers.

pokemon.name: Vullaby
pokemon.description: They tend to guard their posteriors with suitable bones they have found. They pursue weak Pokémon.

pokemon.name: Mandibuzz
pokemon.description: Watching from the sky, they swoop to strike weakened Pokémon on the ground. They decorate themselves with bones.

pokemon.name: Heatmor
pokemon.description: Using their very hot, flame-covered tongues, they burn through Durant's steel bodies and consume their insides.

pokemon.name: Durant
pokemon.description: Durant dig nests in mountains. They build their complicated, interconnected tunnels in mazes.

pokemon.name: Deino
pokemon.description: They cannot see, so they tackle and bite to learn about their surroundings. Their bodies are covered in wounds.

pokemon.name: Zweilous
pokemon.description: Since their two heads do not get along and compete with each other for food, they always eat too much.

pokemon.name: Hydreigon
pokemon.description: The heads on their arms do not have brains. They use all three heads to consume and destroy everything.

pokemon.name: Larvesta
pokemon.description: The base of volcanoes is where they make their homes. They shoot fire from their five horns to repel attacking enemies.

pokemon.name: Volcarona
pokemon.description: A sea of fire engulfs the surroundings of their battles, since they use their six wings to scatter their ember scales.

pokemon.name: Cobalion
pokemon.description: It has a body and heart of steel. Its glare is sufficient to make even an unruly Pokémon obey it.

pokemon.name: Terrakion
pokemon.description: Its charge is strong enough to break through a giant castle wall in one blow. This Pokémon is spoken of in legends.

pokemon.name: Virizion
pokemon.description: Its head sprouts horns as sharp as blades. Using whirlwind-like movements, it confounds and swiftly cuts opponents.

pokemon.name: Tornadus
pokemon.description: Tornadus expels massive energy from its tail, causing severe storms. Its power is great enough to blow houses away.

pokemon.name: Thundurus
pokemon.description: The spikes on its tail discharge immense bolts of lightning. It flies around the Unova region firing off lightning bolts.

pokemon.name: Reshiram
pokemon.description: When Reshiram's tail flares, the heat energy moves the atmosphere and changes the world's weather.

pokemon.name: Zekrom
pokemon.description: This Pokémon appears in legends. In its tail, it has a giant generator that creates electricity.

pokemon.name: Landorus
pokemon.description: The energy that comes pouring from its tail increases the nutrition in the soil, making crops grow to great size.

pokemon.name: Kyurem
pokemon.description: It generates a powerful, freezing energy inside itself, but its body became frozen when the energy leaked out.

pokemon.name: Keldeo
pokemon.description: It crosses the world, running over the surfaces of oceans and rivers. It appears at scenic waterfronts.

pokemon.name: Meloetta
pokemon.description: Many famous songs have been inspired by the melodies that Meloetta plays.

pokemon.name: Genesect
pokemon.description: This ancient bug Pokémon was altered by Team Plasma. They upgraded the cannon on its back.
